    "title": "Principal Plant Manager at Jindal Steel & Power Asia Pacific Associates",
    "description": "Join the Jindal Steel & Power Asia Pacific Associates family as a Plant Manager in Patna. We believe in empowering our employees with the tools, training, and environment they need to succeed.\n\nAbout Jindal Steel & Power Asia Pacific Associates:\nJindal Steel & Power Asia Pacific Associates is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Monitor equipment performance and coordinate preventive maintenance\n• Ensure environmental compliance and waste management\n• Coordinate with design and engineering teams on product improvements\n• Implement lean manufacturing and continuous improvement initiatives\n• Prepare production cost analysis and efficiency reports\n• Ensure product quality meets internal and customer specifications\n• Coordinate with logistics for dispatching finished goods\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• BPharm / MPharm / PharmD\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in AutoCAD\n• Proficiency in PLC/SCADA\n• Proficiency in GD&T\n• Proficiency in Project Management\n• Proficiency in APQP\n• Proficiency in Statistical Process Control\n• Proficiency in SolidWorks\n• Proficiency in FMEA\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Flexible working hours\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Patna, Bihar, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Jindal Steel & Power Asia Pacific Associates!",
